post_text:
The Friends of Otis Library are giving out free books to families who participate in the downtown drop off summer meal program run by the Norwich Public Schools.

Books will be handed out on Fridays from 11:30 am - 11:45 am in front of the Norwich Bulletin office on Railroad Avenue in Norwich.

Books are sorted according to age and placed in plastic bags. Members of the Friends of Otis will approach vehicles to ask if people are interested. If so, they will ask the ages of children and then provide them with the appropriate books. All Otis representatives will be wearing masks.

post_text:
All NPS FAMILIES: Governor Ned Lamont today announced that due to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, he is ordering in-person classes at all K-12 public school facilities in Connecticut to remain canceled for the rest of the 2019-2020 academic year and continue providing distance learning during this period. Schools will also be required to continue providing meals to children under the school lunch and breakfast programs for consumption at home, as they have been throughout this emergency.

More information about next steps will come later today.
text:
All NPS FAMILIES: Governor Ned Lamont today announced that due to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, he is ordering in-person classes at all K-12 public school facilities in Connecticut to remain canceled for the rest of the 2019-2020 academic year and continue providing distance learning during this period. Schools will also be required to continue providing meals to children under the school lunch and breakfast programs for consumption at home, as they have been throughout this emergency.

More information about next steps will come later today.

post_text:
Dear NPS Families & Staff - Please consider taking this brief survey. Your voice matters! Norwich's voice matters!

Thought Exchange Link: https://my.thoughtexchange.com/493894984.

The Commissioner of Education has enlisted the help of the six Regional Education Service Centers (RESC) to form teams of Connecticut education stakeholders for the purpose of gathering, analyzing, and sharing the issues, concerns, and ideas related to the process of reopening schools. An online tool will be used to make the gathering of feedback more efficient and to reflect all the different regions and constituent groups across the state. The tool, "ThoughtExchange," is entirely confidential and anonymous to use. Your participation and feedback are essential to the process and necessary for our State leaders to consider as decisions are made about reopening our schools. I encourage everyone to use the link below to share your thoughts and help evaluate the critical issues.

The third grade students wrote letters and drew pictures for the troops in Kuwait and Niger, Africa. Mrs. Hanner's daughter, Erica, is a Washington Redskins cheerleader and brought the letters with her on a recent Military tour. The soldiers were thrilled to hear from our children back in the US!

All "Norwich Public Schools" are closed today, Wednesday, December 11, 2019.

Norwich public schools are closed today. The heaviest snow is predicted to fall between 8 & 11am with icy roads forming underneath. That means a 2-hour delay would have put our elementary students on the road in the very worst weather scenario. Safety is our first priority.
